https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fburger-king-lawsuit-whoppers-look-bigger-meatier-menus-dismiss-food-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EBurger%20King's%20signature%20Whopper%3C%2Fa%3E%20based%20on%20%26quot%3Bfalse%20and%20misleading%20advertising%20concerning%20the%20size%20and%2For%20the%20amount%20of%20ingredients.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20statement%20to%20Business%20Insider%2C%20Burger%20King%20denied%20the%20claims.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20plaintiffs'%20claims%20are%20false%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20spokesperson%20for%20the%20company%20told%20BI.%20%26quot%3BThe%20flame-grilled%20beef%20patties%20portrayed%20in%20our%20advertising%20are%20the%20same%20patties%20used%20in%20the%20millions%20of%20burgers%20we%20serve%20to%20guests%20across%20the%20US.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBurger%20King%20filed%20a%20motion%20to%20dismiss%20the%20lawsuit%20in%20May%202022%2C%20two%20months%20after%20it%20was%20first%20filed.%20It%20argued%20that%20since%20every%20burger%20is%20hand-made%20at%20the%20restaurant%2C%20the%20%26quot%3Blook%26quot%3B%20of%20each%20sandwich%20%26quot%3Bnecessarily%20will%20differ.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUS%20Southern%20Florida%20District%20Judge%20Roy%20Altman%2C%20however%2C%20said%20in%20his%20ruling%20on%20Monday%20that%20he%20would%20allow%20the%20plaintiff's%20claims%20of%20negligent%20misrepresentation%20to%20move%20forward.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20some%20states%2C%20the%20law%20requires%20that%20a%20customer%20have%20a%20%26quot%3Bspecial%20relationship%26quot%3B%20with%20a%20company%20to%20sue%20it%20for%20misrepresentation%20in%20ads.%20The%20law%20defines%20a%20special%20relationship%20as%20requiring%20a%20%26quot%3Bposition%20of%20confidence%20or%20trust%2C%26quot%3B%20like%20with%20a%20lawyer%20or%20engineer.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EA%20food%20service%20business%20would%20not%20typically%20fall%20into%20this%20category.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EBut%20Florida%20law%20does%20not%20have%20this%20requirement%2C%20Altman%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAltman%20said%20Burger%20King's%20lawyers%20were%20%26quot%3Bresisting%20the%20common-sense%20reading%20of%20Florida%20law%26quot%3B%20by%20suggesting%20that%20Burger%20King%20could%20not%20be%20liable%20based%20on%20the%20absence%20of%20a%20special%20relationship.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Russo%20Firm%2C%20a%20class%20action%20law%20firm%20representing%20the%20plaintiffs%2C%20wrote%20in%20a%20blog%20post%20that%20Altman's%20ruling%20was%20%26quot%3Bsignificant.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20court's%20decision%20underscores%20the%20importance%20of%20truthful%20advertising%20and%20may%20set%20a%20precedent%20for%20how%20fast-food%20chains%20represent%20their%20products%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20post%20says.%20%26quot%3BThe%20outcome%20of%20this%20case%20could%20have%20broader%20implications%20for%20marketing%20standards%20within%20the%20industry.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Whopper%20lawsuit%20is%20the%20latest%20example%20of%20false-advertising%20claims%20targeting%20fast-food%20chains.%20In%202023%2C%20for%20example%2C%20a%20federal%20judge%20in%20Brooklyn%20dismissed%20a%20similar%20false%20advertising%20lawsuit%20against%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmcdonalds-wendys-burgers-look-bigger-in-ads-lawsuit-dismissed-judge-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EWendy's%20and%20McDonald's%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20accused%20the%20restaurants%20of%20marketing%20their%20burgers%20as%20larger%20than%20reality.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUS%20District%20Judge%20Hector%20Gonzalez%20said%20in%20his%20ruling%20for%20that%20case%20that%20the%20plaintiff%20did%20not%20prove%20that%20a%20reasonable%20consumer%20would%20have%20been%20misled%20by%20the%20ads.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlso%20in%202023%2C%20a%20man%20filed%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fman-sues-buffalo-wild-wings-says-boneless-wings-are-nuggets-2023-3%3F_gl%3D1*exf9jo*_ga*MTE5MjEwODAwMC4xNjI5MTI2OTQw*_ga_E21CV80ZCZ*MTY3OTM0MDg