3E%3Cli%3EAmong%20the%20interns%20he's%20mentored%2C%20those%20who%20stood%20out%20were%20willing%20to%20be%20bold.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EDoing%20good%20work%20isn't%20enough%20to%20get%20you%20promoted%2C%20says%20Ryan%20Peterman%2C%20an%20engineer%20at%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-code-meta-microsoft-google-llamacon-engineers-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMeta%3C%2Fa%3E.%20You%20also%20have%20to%20make%20sure%20everyone%20knows%20about%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you%20go%20and%20build%20this%20amazing%20feature%20that%20nobody%20knows%20about%2C%20it%20doesn't%20matter%20how%20good%20it%20is%2C%20you're%20not%20going%20to%20get%20any%20recognition%20for%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20Peterman%20said%20during%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3D_ZJydseTOts%26t%3D1332s%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%20talk%20at%20UCLA%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20so%2C%20how%20do%20you%20advocate%20for%20yourself%20after%20you've%20done%20great%20work%2C%20which%20is%20the%20hard%20part%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPeterman%20worked%20at%20Instagram%20for%20six%20years%2C%20climbing%20to%20staff%20software%20engineer%20before%20changing%20focus%20to%20AI%20training%20infrastructure%20at%20Meta.%20He's%20also%20the%20author%20of%20The%20Developing%20Dev%20newsletter%2C%20which%20offers%20career%20advice%20to%20engineers%20without%20their%20own%20mentors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMaking%20your%20accomplishments%20as%20public%20as%20possible%20is%20the%20key%20%26quot%3Blast%20few%20percent%26quot%3B%20of%20climbing%20the%20career%20ladder%2C%20Peterman%20said.%20That%20can%20be%20as%20simple%20as%20writing%20a%20social%20media%20post%20or%20mentioning%20your%20success%20in%20a%20meeting%2C%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20a%20lot%20of%20people%20miss%20this%2C%20especially%20if%20they're%20more%20introverted%20or%20they're%20more%20quiet%2C%20just%20taking%20that%20last%20step%20on%20after%20the%20good%20work%2C%26quot%3B%20Peterman%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOverperforming%20in%20your%20current%20position%20isn't%20enough%2C%20Peterman%20said.%20He%20gives%20the%20example%20of%20a%20junior%20engineer%20who's%20%26quot%3Bdoing%2010%20times%20as%20many%20features%26quot%3B%20as%20the%20rest%20of%20their%20peers.%20Though%20they're%20likely%20to%20receive%20a%20positive%20performance%20review%2C%20they%20haven't%20proved%20that%20they're%20ready%20to%20take%20on%20senior%20responsibilities%20%E2%80%94%20only%20that%20they're%20extremely%20competent%20at%20tackling%20their%20current%20workload.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20your%20manager%20is%20looking%20to%20fill%20out%20like%20the%20rubric%20for%20the%20next%20level%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20none%20of%20the%20things%20will%20be%20checked%20off%2C%26quot%3B%20Peterman%20said.%20%26quot%3BThere's%20nothing%20about%20initiative%20or%20doing%20anything%20that's%20expected%20of%20the%20mid-level.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIdeally%2C%20he%20added%2C%20you'll%20have%20a%20solid%20grasp%20of%20the%20%26quot%3Bbehaviors%26quot%3B%20exhibited%20by%20engineers%20at%20the%20level%20you're%20looking%20to%20reach%20%E2%80%94%20and%20will%20look%20to%20take%20on%20projects%20that%20allow%20you%20to%20showcase%20them.%20If%20you're%20lost%20as%20to%20what%20your%20organization%20might%20be%20looking%20for%20in%20more%20senior%20engineers%2C%20Peterman%20suggests%20talking%20to%20your%20supervisor.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20was%20really%2C%20really%20eager%20to%20get%20promoted%2C%20and%20so%20I%20was%20constantly%20talking%20to%20my%20manager%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BAs%20soon%20as%20I%20got%20promoted%20to%20one%20level%2C%20I%20was%20like%2C%20'Okay%2C%20what's%20the%20next%20level%3F%20What%20can%20I%20do%3F'%20Maybe%20that%20was%20annoying%20for%20my%20manager%2C%20but%20he%20was%20really%20helpful%20in%20teaching%20me%20what%20were%20the%20things%20that%20I%20needed%20to%20pick%20up.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAbove%20all%20else%2C%20he%20added%2C%20it's%20in%20your%20best%20interest%20to%20be%20as%20visible%20as%20possible.%20In%20the%20course%20of%20his%20time%20at%20Meta%2C%20Peterman%20has%20taken%20on%20five%20interns%20%E2%80%94%20those%20who%20stood%20out%20were%20just%20more%20willing%20to%20be%20bold.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20I%20think%20about%20the%20ones%20that%20were%20rock%20stars%2C%20they%20had%20the%20audacity%20to%20propose%20improvements%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BEven%20though%20obviously%20I'm%20the%20more%20senior%20person%2C%20they%20had%20the%20audacity%20to%20ask%20questions%2C%20propose%20improvements.%20Sometimes%20they%20weren't%20right%2C%20but%20I%20could%20see%20the%20logic%20%E2%80%94%20but%20many%20times%20they%20were.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmeta-engineer-advice-how-to-get-promoted-2025-5%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1746815590000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F681cff4fc6ad288d14806b8d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmeta-engineer-advice-how-to-get-promoted-2025-5%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Ryan%20Peterman%2C%20who%20also%20writes%20The%20Developing%20Dev%20newsletter%2C%20says%20making%20sure%20people%20are%20aware%20of%20your%20accomplishments%20is%20key.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22sperkel%40insider.com%20(Sarah%20Perkel)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A126%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmeta-engineer-advice-how-to-get-promoted-2025-5%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Texas%20is%20on%20the%20verge%20of%20handing%20Tesla%20and%20other%20big%20businesses%20a%20major%20win%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Photo%20collage%20of%20Elon%20Musk%2C%20Texas%20State%20Capitol%20building%20in%20Austin%20and%20money%20falling.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F681d15123fe8d39283655b13%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EGetty%20Images%3B%20Chip%20Somodevilla%2FAP%20Photo%3B%20Tyler%20Le%2FBI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ETexas%20lawmakers%20have%20passed%20bills%20to%20reduce%20the%20influence%20of%20small%20shareholders.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EBackers%20say%20the%20bills%20would%20attract%20companies%2C%20while%20critics%20call%20it%20a%20power%20grab%20by%20corporate%20insiders.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ELawmakers%20say%20ExxonMobil's%20board%20shake-up%20and%20Elon%20Musk's%20pay%20lawsuit%20inspired%20the%20legislation.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20Delaware%20rebukes%20Elon%20Musk%20over%20his%20pay%20package%2C%20Texas%20is%20now%20offering%20corporate%20America%20a%20path%20to%20sidestep%20legal%20challenges%20from%20most%20of%20its%20shareholders.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20past%20two%20months%2C%20lawmakers%20have%20pushed%20through%20a%20pair%20of%20bills%20they%20say%20would%20bring%20more%20businesses%20to%20the%20Lone%20Star%20State.%20Senate%20Bill%2029%20would%20make%20it%20harder%20for%20shareholders%20to%20sue%20companies%2C%20while%20Senate%20Bill%201057%20would%20raise%20the%20bar%20for%20bringing%20resolutions%20at%20annual%20meetings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESB%2029%20would%20apply%20to%20many%20big%20companies%20incorporated%20in%20Texas%2C%20like%20Tesla%20and%20Southwest%20Airlines.%20SB%201057%20could%20apply%20to%20businesses%20that%20are%20merely%20headquartered%20in%20Texas%2C%20like%20AT%26amp%3BT%20and%20Waste%20Management%2C%20even%20if%20they're%20legally%20registered%20elsewhere.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20have%20moved%20quickly%20with%20virtually%20no%20organized%20opposition%2C%20with%20both%20measures%20now%20awaiting%20Gov.%20Greg%20Abbott's%20signature.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHis%20office%20told%20Business%20Insider%20he%20wanted%20to%20strengthen%20businesses%20and%20would%20%26quot%3Breview%20any%20proposal%26quot%3B%20lawmakers%20send%20to%20his%20desk.%20He%20has%20previously%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Fopinion%2Fforget-delaware-yall-street-is-open-for-business-texas-corporate-law-cb9088d1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esignaled%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20he%20would%20sign%20SB%2029.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChris%20Babcock%2C%20a%20Dallas%20lawyer%20who%20helped%20draft%20SB%2029%2C%20told%20BI%20that%20a%20wide%20variety%20of%20businesses%20and%20experts%20shaped%20the%20bill%2C%20which%20he%20said%20he%20viewed%20as%20balanced.%20State%20Sen.%20Bryan%20Hughes%2C%20a%20Republican%20and%20a%20major%20backer%20of%20SB%201057%2C%20said%20it%20was%20meant%20to%20stop%20politicized%20attacks%20on%20Texas%20businesses.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECritics%2C%20meanwhile%2C%20said%20the%20bills%20could%20gut%20minority%20shareholder%20rights%20and%20make%20Texas%20a%20haven%20for%20corporate%20officers%2C%20such%20as%20Musk%2C%20who%20have%20unusually%20large%20ownership%20stakes%20and%20influence%20over%20their%20businesses.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere's%20a%20famous%20quote%20from%20John%20Dingell%2C%20the%20former%20Michigan%20congressman%2C%20who%20said%2C%20'If%20you%20write%20the%20substance%20and%20you%20let%20me%20write%20the%20procedure%2C%20I'll%20screw%20you%20every%20time.'%20That's%20exactly%20what's%20happening%20here%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Joel%20Fleming%2C%20a%20lawyer%20who%20represents%20investors%20in%20governance%20disputes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20other%20words%2C%20Texas%20wouldn't%20be%20changing%20the%20standards%20corporate%20boards%20are%20held%20to%2C%20Fleming%20believes%20%E2%80%94%20but%20would%20make%20it%20very%20hard%20for%20regular%20shareholders%20to%20hold%20them%20accountable%20if%20they%20break%20the%20rules.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22c911b049-412a-490e-bd28-58525f10bea0%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ETexas%20lends%20a%20hand%20to%20corporate%20managers%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20publicly%20traded%20companies%20opt%20in%2C%20SB%2029%20would%20give%20boards%20of%20directors%20significantly%20more%20legal%20protection%20and%20make%20it%20more%20difficult%20for%20investors%20to%20sue%20directors%2C%20effectively%20preventing%20high-profile%20shareholder%20lawsuits%20like%20the%20one%20that%20saw%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjudge-strikes-down-elon-musk-tesla-pay-package-second-time-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDelaware%20judge%3C%2Fa%3E%20strike%20down%20Musk's%20pay%20package.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBabcock%20called%20the%20Tesla%20case%2C%20which%20is%20on%20appeal%2C%20an%20%26quot%3Baccelerator.%26quot%3B%20Other%20decisions%20by%20the%20state's%20chancery%20court%20involving%20the%20companies%20Moelis%20and%20Activision%20%26quot%3Bchallenged%20long-standing%20corporate%20practices%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20and%20also%20drove%20discussions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHow%20can%20you%20have%20confidence%20in%20Delaware%20judges%3F%26quot%3B%20said%20Eric%20Lentell%2C%20the%20top%20lawyer%20at%20Archer%20Aviation%20who%20testified%20in%20favor%20of%20SB%2029%20and%20whose%20company%20is%20being%20sued%20in%20Delaware.%20%26quot%3BA%20shareholder%20vote%20was%20essentially%20ignored%26quot%3B%20when%20Tesla%20investors%20tried%20to%20ratify%20Musk's%20compensation%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMusk%20and%20Tesla%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20requests%20for%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESB%201057%2C%20meanwhile%2C%20would%20raise%20the%20bar%20for%20shareholder%20resolutions.%20It%20would%20require%20shareholders%20to%20own%20a%203%25%20stake%20or%20%241%20million%20in%20stock%20and%20to%20gather%20support%20from%20holders%20of%20two-thirds%20of%20the%20company's%20shares%20before%20submitting%20a%20proposal.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJames%20McRitchie%2C%20a%20small%20investor%20from%20California%20who%20opposes%20the%20bill%2C%20said%20Texas%20was%20%26quot%3Bleading%20the%20race%20to%20the%20bottom.%26quot%3B%20He%20said%20soliciting%20support%20from%20other%20investors%20could%20cost%20millions%20with%20a%20company%20like%20Tesla%20and%20deter%20all%20but%20the%20wealthiest%20investors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHughes%20cited%20the%20small%20hedge%20fund%20Engine%20No.%201's%20successful%20campaign%20to%20reshape%20Exxon's%20board%20of%20directors%20in%202021%20as%20an%20influence%2C%20though%20SB%201057%20doesn't%20apply%20to%20director%20nominations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20spokesperson%20for%20Engine%20No.%201%20declined%20to%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAT%26amp%3BT%20and%20Nasdaq%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcapitol.texas.gov%2Ftlodocs%2F89R%2Fwitlistmtg%2Fpdf%2FC5702025031009001.PDF%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eregistered%20support%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20SB%2029.%20The%20Texas%20Stock%20Exchange%2C%20a%20startup%20trying%20to%20woo%20listings%20away%20from%20New%20York%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcapitol.texas.gov%2Ftlodocs%2F89R%2Fwitlistmtg%2Fpdf%2FC5102025031808001.PDF%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebacked%3C%2Fa%3E%20both%20bills.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20bill%2C%20Senate%20Bill%202337%2C%20which%20isn't%20as%20far%20along%2C%20targets%20certain%20recommendations%20from%20proxy%20advisors.%20Hughes%20said%20companies%20like%20ISS%20and%20Glass%20Lewis%20had%20recommended%20that%20institutional%20investors%20vote%20their%20shares%20for%20environmental-%20and%20diversity-motivated%20reasons%20that%20may%20not%20actually%20increase%20the%20value%20of%20their%20shares.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EISS%20and%20Glass%20Lewis%20didn't%20respond%20to%20requests%20for%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22c3504c0b-2813-410d-8ad2-46a69e837ffa%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E'Dexit'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EHughes%20said%20SB%2029%20would%20build%20on%20last%20year's%20creation%20of%20a%20specialized%20Texas%20business%20court.%20He%20referred%20to%20the%20bill%20as%20%26quot%3BDexit%26quot%3B%20at%20a%20hearing%2C%20a%20nod%20to%20companies%20like%20Tesla%20and%20Tripadvisor%20moving%20out%20of%20Delaware.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDelaware's%20defenders%20say%20its%20laws%20are%20applied%20predictably%20and%20its%20courts%20are%20run%20by%20expert%20judges%20who%20are%20neither%20pro-management%20nor%20pro-shareholder.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20think%20we're%20putting%20the%20last%20pieces%20together%20to%20make%20Texas%20an%20attractive%20place%20for%20doing%20business%2C%26quot%3B%20Hughes%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBrian%20Quinn%2C%20a%20law%20professor%20at%20Boston%20College%2C%20said%20the%20bills%20would%20give%20corporate%20managers%20too%20much%20power%20for%20investors%20to%20be%20comfortable.%20He%20said%20they%20would%20turn%20Texas%20into%20a%20%26quot%3Brogues'%20gallery%26quot%3B%20like%20Nevada%2C%20which%20has%20been%20criticized%20over%20its%20lax%2C%20pro-management%20corporate%20laws.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTexas%20isn't%20competing%20with%20Delaware%2C%26quot%3B%20Quinn%20said.%20%26quot%3BTexas%20is%20competing%20with%20Nevada.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBabcock%20said%20Texas%20would%20still%20have%20stricter%20shareholder%20oversight%20than%20Nevada%2C%20adding%20that%20Texas%20directors%20must%20remain%20loyal%20to%20companies%20and%20could%20be%20more%20easily%20removed%20by%20shareholders.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGlenn%20Hamer%2C%20who%20leads%20the%20Texas%20Association%20of%20Business%2C%20said%20at%20a%20hearing%20in%20March%20that%20%26quot%3BDelaware%20has%20blown%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20have%20the%20best%20economy%20in%20the%20galaxy%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BIf%20you%20have%20an%20internal%20issue%2C%20are%20you%20going%20to%20be%20better%20treated%20in%20Delaware%2C%20or%20are%20you%20going%20to%20be%20better%20treated%20in%20a%20state%20that%20has%20become%20the%20economic%20engine%20of%20the%20United%20States%20of%20America%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EHave%20a%20tip%3F%20Contact%20this%20reporter%20via%20Signal%20a